Class Event

  • java.lang.Object
    • cnss.simulator.Event

  • public class Event
extends java.lang.Object
    The Event class which represents an event to occur in the simulator.
    Version:
    1.0, September 2020
    Author:
    System's team of the Department of Informatics of FCT/UNL based on a, preliminary version by Adam Greenhalgh of UCL

    • Constructor Detail

      • Event

        public Event(Event.EventType op,
             int t,
             long id,
             java.lang.String[] a)
        Event constructor, which takes the name and UUID of the event, the time the event is to occur, and a list of arguments to the event.
        Parameters:
        op - the name (type) of the event
        t - the time the event is to occur
        id - an unique id of the event, t << 32+id is the UUID of the event
        a - the arguments to the event.

      • Event

        public Event(Event.EventType op,
             int t,
             long id,
             java.lang.String[] a,
             Packet p,
             int n,
             int itfc)
        Event constructor, which takes the name and UUID of the event, the time the event is to occur, and a list of arguments to the event.
        Parameters:
        op - the name (type) of the event
        t - the time the event is to occur
        id - an unique id of the event, t << 32+id is the UUID of the event
        a - the arguments to the event.
        p - a Packet associated with this event.
        n - a node associated with this event.
        itfc - an interface of the above node associated with this event.
